  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Soak your <strong>skewers</strong> in <strong>cold water</strong> (this stops them from burning whilst cooking!)</p><p>Cut your<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips, then add them to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and put in the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 15 min</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1713879347078-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1713879347078-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1713879347078-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1713879347078-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1713879347078-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong> and peel and grate (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add <strong>half </strong>the <strong>grated garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>to a bowl with your <strong>chicken thighs</strong>, <strong>Mediterranean-style seasoning</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>– these are your <strong>marinated chicken thighs</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1713879350483-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1713879350483-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1713879350483-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1713879350483-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1713879350483-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Thread the <strong>marinated chicken thighs</strong> onto the <strong>soaked</strong> <strong>skewers</strong> in a snake-like fashion – these are your <strong>marinated chicken skewers</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1713879383602-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1713879383602-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1713879383602-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1713879383602-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1713879383602-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the tray[s] with the chips from the oven and add<strong> half </strong>the<strong> sliced shallot </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), then place the <strong>marinated chicken skewers</strong> on top</p><p>Tip: This will allow your chips to soak up all the juices and give them extra flavour!</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for 22-25 min or until the chicken is slightly charred and cooked through (no pink meat!) – these are your <strong>chicken souvlaki skewers</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
